title: James Webb telescope completes optical alignment, ready for final instrument calibration phase of commissioning

title: Four astronauts arrive at space station for long-term stay
summary: Three Americans and one Italian astronaut floated into the International Space Station late Wednesday after a nearly 16-hour transit aboard a SpaceX crew capsule from a launch pad on Florida’s Space Coast, ready for a research expedition scheduled to last at least four-and-a-half months.
